definition: to use/by means of/according to/in order to/because of/at (a certain date or place)
abbr. for Israel 以色列[Yi3 se4 lie4]
horse/CL:匹[pi3]/horse or cavalry piece in Chinese chess/knight in Western chess
surname Ma/abbr. for Malaysia 馬來西亞|马来西亚[Ma3 lai2 xi1 ya4]

sentences.english: Christians believe that Emanuel is the prophet Isaiah's prophecy of the Messiah.
sentences.chinese: 基督徒相信以马内利就是先知以赛亚所预言的弥赛亚。

sentences.english: Its outspread wings will cover the breadth of your land, O Immanuel !
sentences.chinese: 以马内利阿，他展开翅膀，遍满你的地。

sentences.english: Emannuel, God is with us, Blessed Redeemer, Living Word.
sentences.chinese: 以马内利，与人同在的神，圣洁的救主，永活的道。

sentences.english: Main page for Little Rock Chinese Immanuel Baptist Church.
sentences.chinese: 小岩城以马内利华语浸信会主页。

sentences.english: The lamb is all the glory Of Immanuel's land.
sentences.chinese: 羔羊荣耀今充满，以马内利之境。

sentences.english: Come, come Emmanuel, O Child of Love and Peace.
sentences.chinese: 以马内利，慈爱和平的婴孩请来临。

definition: (third person pronoun for a divine being)
Abba (Aramaic word father)/by ext. God the Father in Christian gospel
Jehovah (biblical name for God, Hebrew: YHWH)/compare Yahweh 雅威[Ya3 wei1] and God 上帝[Shang4 di4]
God (in Catholicism)/abbr. for 天主教[Tian1 zhu3 jiao4], Catholicism
